[2026-04-29 17:31:07,951][INFO][social_topic_miner.pipeline]: For Sampled Topic id 0: keyword is ['ai', 'app', 'just', 'ive', 'models', 'way', 'pro', 'dont'] and posts are [{'text': "How to stop safari from changing the color of the address bar constantly? Disabling website tinting does nothing I took 4 screenshots from screen recording of scrolling cnn and it changes constantly. It's honestly super distracting and is by far the worst part of the new ios design EDIT: So I just updated from ios 26.3 to 26.4.2 as a hail mary and now the address bar hasn't changed since. I can't say for sure that was it because I did mess around a bunch in settings but if you have a similar problem just try updating", 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 0, 'engagement_norm': 0.43820224719101125, 'post_id': '1sysiki', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 08:13:06+00:00'}, {'text': 'Now Claude payments are throwing Stripe internal server errors too, what is going on? A few days ago I posted about Anthropic account bans, no clear refund process, and accounts being stuck in limbo. [ I thought that was already messy enough. Now there’s another problem: trying to pay for Claude through their Stripe checkout is giving an **Internal Server Error**. This does not look like a normal bank issue, because previous payments worked before. Something seems to have changed on Claude/Stripe’s payment setup, and now payments that used to go through are just failing with a generic error. So let me get this straight: Accounts can get banned with no clear explanation. Refunds are unclear or missing. Support is slow or nonexistent. And now even paying for Claude is broken? For a company charging premium subscription prices, the billing and support experience feels way too unstable. Is anyone else getting this Stripe internal server error when trying to pay for Claude?', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 1, 'engagement_norm': 0.5308988764044944, 'post_id': '1sz1ar5', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 14:59:30+00:00'}, {'text': 'Can anyone guess which is Nano Banana and which is GPT Image 2, and which is better?', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 2, 'engagement_norm': 0.7696629213483146, 'post_id': '1syktnf', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 01:41:25+00:00'}, {'text': 'Opus 4.7: Are these first signs of model collapse? I keep getting shocked by how bad the reasoning of Opus 4.7 is. It still seems fine for programming tasks, but when I ask it to advise me about things, it often produces illogical, nonsensical and flatout wrong responses and shows that it didn\'t understand simple concepts we had just discussed in the conversation. It is so much worse than previous models that I\'m wondering whether we might be starting to see signs of model collapse: this term refers to more and more content on the internet being AI generated and how problematic it is to use such content as training data for new models. And it\'s not easy to filter out AI content. We all know how unreliable AI detectors are, so the more AI content is on the internet the more our training data becomes "infected". Have we reached peak LLM performance and are degrading from here?', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 3, 'engagement_norm': 0.6741573033707865, 'post_id': '1sysm4v', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 08:19:14+00:00'}, {'text': 'Unable to download the latest iOS update I have an iPhone 12 and 64 GB storage. I have had the phone since 2022 and battery replaced a year ago. The storage was quite full however I managed to offload and uninstall apps to get it to 45 as it told me I need 17 gb and it still won’t download. I removed everything and Reddit. I just reinstalled Reddit to come on here and ask. Idk what to do. Any advice?', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 4, 'engagement_norm': 0.21910112359550563, 'post_id': '1szcoaq', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 21:44:57+00:00'}, {'text': "Instructions for Gemini is useless? I can't get Gemini to stop prompting me for a follow-up response every time I say anything.", 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 5, 'engagement_norm': 0.6123595505617978, 'post_id': '1syjc2m', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 00:34:40+00:00'}] 
