orm": 0.8938547486033519, "post_id": "1sz522l", "created_at": "2026-04-29 17:11:58+00:00"}, {"text": "Olivia Rodrigo to her best friend and \u2018Bizaardvark\u2019 co-star Madison Hu: \u201cMadison, you're the longest love of my life besides my parents.\u201d", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 4, "engagement_norm": 0.8044692737430168, "post_id": "1szc8o4", "created_at": "2026-04-29 21:28:05+00:00"}, {"text": "\u2018Malcolm in the Middle\u2019 Star Justin Berfield Tells Paparazzi to Leave Dewey Actor Eric Per Sullivan Alone After He Turned Down the Reboot: \u2018I Actually Feel Bad\u2019", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 5, "engagement_norm": 0.9162011173184358, "post_id": "1syoau0", "created_at": "2026-04-29 04:23:35+00:00"}]}, {"topic_id": 2, "headline": "Atl\u00e9tico Madrid and Arsenal Battle to a Draw in UCL Clash", "category": "Sports", "short_summary": "In a tense match, Atl\u00e9tico Madrid and Arsenal ended in a stalemate, setting the stage for an exciting return leg.", "long_summary": "The UEFA Champions League match between Atl\u00e9tico Madrid and Arsenal concluded with both teams unable to find the back of the net, ending in a 0-0 draw. Despite a controversial moment where Koke's foul on Gabriel went unpunished, the defensive strategies of both teams were on full display. With only one shot on target in the first half, the match highlighted the importance of defense over attack, leaving fans eager for the next encounter.", "keywords": ["atltico", "breaking", "atltico madrid", "pitch", "chance", "arsenal", "simeone", "penalty"], "key_points": ["Koke's foul on Gabriel did not result in a penalty.", "Both teams showcased strong defensive performances throughout the match."], "n_posts": 44, "n_perspectives": 4, "representative_posts": [{"text": "\ud83d\udea8 BREAKING: Koke got his entire arm around Gabriel but there was NO penalty given!", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 0, "engagement_norm": 0.9539473684210527, "post_id": "2049570938098729093", "created_at": "2026-04-29 19:26:05+00:00"}, {"text": "\ud83d\udcf8 - That was an INSANELY well taken penalty!", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 0, "engagement_norm": 0.8486842105263158, "post_id": "2049583959734952011", "created_at": "2026-04-29 20:17:50+00:00"}, {"text": "\ud83d\udcf8 - Only 1 shot on target in this match in 35 minutes so far. Yesterday there were 3 goals already in minute 35.", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 1, "engagement_norm": 0.7894736842105263, "post_id": "2049573663939113118", "created_at": "2026-04-29 19:36:55+00:00"}, {"text": "\ud83d\udcf8 - Noni Madueke did an attempt to head the ball but instead knocked out his own teammate.", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 1, "engagement_norm": 0.5263157894736842, "post_id": "2049570376833700005", "created_at": "2026-04-29 19:23:51+00:00"}, {"text": "\ud83d\udcf8 - If yesterday was about how to attack, then tonight is all about how to defend. Look how great Atl\u00e9tico Madrid defend.", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 2, "engagement_norm": 0.5197368421052632, "post_id": "2049570197153935555", "created_at": "2026-04-29 19:23:08+00:00"}, {"text": "\ud83d\udcf8 - And now Atl\u00e9tico Madrid are attacking and LOOK how quick Arsenal have their entire team back in their own box!", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 2, "engagement_norm": 0.7368421052631579, "post_id": "2049571984917315862", "created_at": "2026-04-29 19:30:15+00:00"}, {"text": "It ends level \u23f1\ufe0f All to play for next week \u2696\ufe0f UCL", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 3, "engagement_norm": 0.9078947368421053, "post_id": "2049594629364863347", "created_at": "2026-04-29 21:00:13+00:00"}, {"text": "\ud83d\udcf8 - BOTH TEAMS ARE READY! THIS IS GOING TO BE ANOTHER ALL-TIMER!", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 3, "engagement_norm": 0.506578947368421, "post_id": "2049564713546117130", "created_at": "2026-04-29 19:01:21+00:00"}]}, {"topic_id": 5, "headline": "Real Madrid in Talks for New Coach Amidst Mourinho Speculation", "category": "Sports", "short_summary": "Real Madrid is reportedly in discussions with Jurgen Klopp to take over as coach, while fans debate the potential return of Jose Mourinho.", "long_summary": "Real Madrid is currently exploring options for their coaching position, with Jurgen Klopp emerging as a leading candidate to accept an offer from the club. Meanwhile, discussions about the possible return of Jose Mourinho have sparked mixed reactions among fans, who reflect on his past successes and the current state of the team. The club's recent struggles have led to speculation about the direction they should take moving forward.", "keywords": ["real", "madrid", "role", "season", "mourinho", "couldve", "talks", "teams"], "key_points": ["Real Madrid is in talks with Jurgen Klopp for the coaching role.", "Fans are divided on the potential return of Jose Mourinho as manager."], "n_posts": 20, "n_perspectives": 4, "representative_posts": [{"text": "Does Mourinho's Win Rate Make Him Perfect for Real Madrid?", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 0, "engagement_norm": 0.388268156424581, "post_id": "1szc7zu", "created_at": "2026-04-29 21:27:23+00:00"}, {"text": "What do you think about Jose Mourinho as manager?", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 0, "engagement_norm": 0.6759776536312849, "post_id": "1syxyww", "created_at": "2026-04-29 12:53:51+00:00"}, {"text": "\ud83d\udea8 BREAKING: Real Madrid now believe that Jurgen Klopp will ACCEPT THE OFFER to become the club's new COACH!", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 1, "engagement_norm": 0.6776315789473685, "post_id": "2049641004869783592", "created_at": "2026-04-30 00:04:30+00:00"}, {"text": "\ud83d\udea8 BREAKING: Real Madrid are in talks with Toni Kroos for his RETURN to the club in a new role with KEY responsibilities!", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 1, "engagement_norm": 0.8355263157894737, "post_id": "2049542897880404443", "created_at": "2026-04-29 17:34:40+00:00"}, {"text": "HERE IT IS : Mbappe 2025/26 Initially, it seems we'll win it all this season. But many blunders cost the whole season. \\>defence crisis \\>poor medical teams \\>too many injuries \\>weak chemistry between players. \\>sacking a great new gen coach mid season \\>dressing room controversies. Apart from that, still the highest goal scorrer back to back season. I hope new season, new manager, will bring the great out of our team, vini,mbappe chemistry must be there next season \ud83e\udef6\ud83c\udffb", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 2, "engagement_norm": 0.6815642458100558, "post_id": "1syp31w", "created_at": "2026-04-29 05:03:25+00:00"}, {"text": "We couldve had it all man Just one transfer. ONE. Even if youre the biggest mbappe glazer, the biggest vini hater, the biggest alonso fan, the biggest ancelotti fan, perez himself whatever, you cant tell you dont sit every once in a while and just ponder on what couldve been if we signed kane when benzema left. In form vini, rodrygo, and jude all playing with kane wouldve been stuff of dreams. He can both score and stat pad and link up perfectly with all his teammates because he has actual good spatial awareness. You never know what wouldve happened since it didnt but i have a strong belief that we couldve went on another threepeat with kane. One transfer couldve sent us beyond the moon and one transfer sent us to the depth of this current hell nonetheless hala madrid", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 2, "engagement_norm": 0.664804469273743, "post_id": "1syjgtb", "created_at": "2026-04-29 00:40:37+00:00"}, {"text": "Atp it\u2019s a self repeating cycle. Honestly, Ik many people are against Jose but realistically I don\u2019t see these entitled players respecting anyone else besides these three. And say what you will our periods of success have been with these three. Is Jose possibly washed ? Perhaps, but I say still give him a. Chance. He\u2019s a great manager for drilling the winning mentality into these players and ain\u2019t no one in the squad will have a bigger ego than him.", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 3, "engagement_norm": 0.7206703910614525, "post_id": "1sykb9f", "created_at": "2026-04-29 01:18:28+00:00"}, {"text": "AMA: The Athletic's Real Madrid reporter, Mario Cortegana Hi everyone! I\u2019m Mario Cortegana, Real Madrid correspondent for The Athletic. I\u2019ve been following the club\u2019s day-to-day since January 2019 in Spain and around the world, and have been fortunate enough to cover their last two Champions League titles and the first Club World Cup ever. I'm delighted to answer your questions for around an hour this Thursday, 30 April, from 5pm BST. Real Madrid news is always fascinating, but I\u2019d say even more so right now, so I look forward to seeing you all here for a good chat! [Mario Cortegana.](", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 3, "engagement_norm": 0.44692737430167595, "post_id": "1szcunh", "created_at": "2026-04-29 21:52:03+00:00"}]}, {"topic_id": 9, "headline": "2026 Miami GP Faces Potential Heavy Rain on Race Day", "category": "Sports", "short_summary": "The upcoming Miami GP is at risk of heavy rainfall and thunderstorms on Sunday, raising concerns for the event's schedule.", "long_summary": "As the 2026 Miami Grand Prix approaches, weather forecasts indicate a significant threat of heavy rain and thunderstorms on race day. While Friday and Saturday are expected to be clear, models suggest that a cold front could bring intense storms, potentially impacting the race. Organizers are reminded of safety protocols regarding lightning, which could lead to event suspensions if necessary.", "keywords": ["event", "heavy", "friday", "day", "2026", "camera", "intense", "events"], "key_points": ["Heavy rainfall and thunderstorms predicted for race day on Sunday.", "Safety protocols in place for lightning detection at the Miami GP."], "n_posts": 13, "n_perspectives": 4, "representative_posts": [{"text": "Colapinto driving a small Kart for Ibuprofen brand Actron", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 0, "engagement_norm": 0.5921787709497207, "post_id": "1sz5u1l", "created_at": "2026-04-29 17:39:01+00:00"}, {"text": "Racing Bull\u2019s special livery for the 2026 Miami GP", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 1, "engagement_norm": 0.9106145251396648, "post_id": "1szez61", "created_at": "2026-04-29 23:18:06+00:00"}, {"text": "PSA: Miami GP camera restrictions Just a friendly reminder to anyone going to the Miami F1 GP and planning to bring your camera, they have pretty strict lens size restrictions. These restrictions are not from the FIA or FOM, each track has different rules. Zandvoort and LAs Vegas don\u2019t allow cameras at all. Other tracks have little to no restrictions.", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 1, "engagement_norm": 0.8715083798882681, "post_id": "1syycle", "created_at": "2026-04-29 13:08:55+00:00"}, {"text": "Why does the weather app do this? Why for a day that is perfectly clear and sunny almost every hour of the day par a (40% chance) shower at midnight does the weather app decide to summarise the day as \u201cheavy rain\u201d? I\u2019ve had multiple instances of almost replanning entire days because I\u2019ve looked at the day summary on weather and thought that the weather is far worse than it actually is.", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 2, "engagement_norm": 0.388268156424581, "post_id": "1sze4c1", "created_at": "2026-04-29 22:42:14+00:00"}, {"text": "2026 Miami GP Early Weather Preview EDIT: I forgot to update the Fahrenheit conversion for the temperature on Sunday, it should read 79o to 84oF. F1 is finally back, and I'm back with a weather forecast, which unfortunately means some interesting weather is expected this weekend. Now that we're within 48 hours of FP1, we can take an early look at the forecast, which I'm calling a \"preview\". Friday and Saturday should be fine, but there is a real threat of heavy rainfall and/or thunderstorms at least on and off on Sunday. We are still five days out, and so a lot can and will change, but we are currently looking at a growing model consensus at a cold front bringing stormy weather on Sunday. The ECMWF/European model is in particular intense, showing a heavy thunderstorm dropping nearly 1 inch (2.5 cm) of rainfall in the three-hour span that the race falls into. Other models are thankfully less intense. We are not yet in range of the high-resolution mesoscale models, which can actually model thunderstorms, but we should be by Friday. I'll be back on Friday morning with a full weekend forecast update, and possibly again on Sunday morning for a race-specific outlook. Finally, I hate to mention this coming off of a month break and two cancellations, but I need to note that most U.S. sporting events are required by contract with workers, the event space, and local government to have plans for lightning in place. I could not find the specific policy for Hard Rock Stadium, but the Miami GP website lists the following: \"When lightning is detected in close proximity of the Miami International Autodrome, the public address system will inform guests where to seek shelter. The event will be suspended if there is an imminent threat.\" My understanding is many outdoor U.S. sporting events have a \"lightning clock\", where any lightning strike or thunder heard within a certain radius of the location (ex: 10 miles) immediately starts a 30 minute countdown, during which the event is suspended and fans/employees are instructed to seek shelter. Every subsequent thunder heard resets that timer, until 30 minutes have passed since the last thunder was heard, after which the event may resume. This does not give a lot of leeway for F1, especially if the storms are slow-moving as they likely will be with a cold front transitioning to stationary. The best hope is that the front and any associated storms fully clear the track by the afternoon, or that they remain heavy showers with no lightning.", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 2, "engagement_norm": 0.6368715083798883, "post_id": "1sz4aou", "created_at": "2026-04-29 16:45:18+00:00"}, {"text": "Aston Martin has once again been seen testing their cyber formula lookin thing at Portimao, where it supposedly set a 1:24 second lap Source is \\_all\\_about\\_cars on instagram", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 3, "engagement_norm": 0.9217877094972067, "post_id": "1sz9u41", "created_at": "2026-04-29 19:59:38+00:00"}, {"text": "[Motorsport] New pre- and post-race F1 shows are coming to Apple TV!", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 3, "engagement_norm": 0.6536312849162011, "post_id": "1sz2rrg", "created_at": "2026-04-29 15:51:09+00:00"}]}, {"topic_id": 6, "headline": "Cristiano Ronaldo Approaches 1000 Career Goals", "category": "Sports", "short_summary": "Cristiano Ronaldo has reached a milestone of 970 career goals, with only 30 remaining to hit the 1000 mark.", "long_summary": "Cristiano Ronaldo continues to impress on the field as he reaches 970 career goals, bringing him closer to the historic milestone of 1000. Fans are eagerly anticipating this achievement, which would further solidify his legacy as one of the greatest footballers of all time. With his current form, many believe he will reach this landmark soon.", "keywords": ["ronaldo", "cristiano", "cristiano ronaldo", "al", "xi", "saudi", "fans", "lead"], "key_points": ["Cristiano Ronaldo has scored 970 career goals.", "He needs 30 more goals to reach the 1000 goal milestone."], "n_posts": 19, "n_perspectives": 6, "representative_posts": [{"text": "2-0 Al Nassr. COMAN DOUBLES THE LEAD AGAINST AL AHLI!!!!!!!!! HE PUTS THE SUNGLASSES ON TO CELEBRATE!!!!!!!!!", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 0, "engagement_norm": 0.868421052631579, "post_id": "2049578482213011671", "created_at": "2026-04-29 19:56:04+00:00"}, {"text": "\ud83d\udcf8 - CRISTIANO RONALDO HAS NOW REACHED 970 CAREER GOALS! 30 GOALS LEFT!", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 1, "engagement_norm": 0.7039473684210527, "post_id": "2049575413978992869", "created_at": "2026-04-29 19:43:52+00:00"}, {"text": "Zayn Malik and his family ask fans to donate to the Palestine Project after knowing fans were sending them flowers bouquets.", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 2, "engagement_norm": 0.7094972067039106, "post_id": "1szdlv5", "created_at": "2026-04-29 22:21:00+00:00"}, {"text": "1-1 Atl\u00e9tico Madrid. GOOOOOOOOOOOOLLLLLL JULIAN ALVAREZ !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! GOL GOL GOL GOL GOL !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! HE DELIVERED VS BARCELONA AND NOW HE DELIVERS VS ARSENAL !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! GAME ON !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! \ud83c\udde6\ud83c\uddf7\ud83d\udcab", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 3, "engagement_norm": 0.5723684210526315, "post_id": "2049583754847441201", "created_at": "2026-04-29 20:17:01+00:00"}, {"text": "\ud83d\udea8 BREAKING: Achraf Hakimi is out for the 2nd leg against Bayern Munich. He got injured last night. Medical tests carried out this afternoon have confirmed a hamstring tear. \u2014", "platform": "twitter", "sub_perspective": 4, "engagement_norm": 0.8421052631578947, "post_id": "2049532696112636043", "created_at": "2026-04-29 16:54:07+00:00"}, {"text": "Saudi Arabia Pulls Funding From LIV Golf. Its Star Players Face a Painful Road Back to The PGA Tour.", "platform": "reddit", "sub_perspective": 5, "engagement_norm": 0.8212290502793296, "post_id": "1szcfq6", "created_at": "2026-04-29 21:35:31+00:00"}]}], "total_posts_processed": 331, "digest": "Lady Gaga is generating excitement as she prepares for the release of three new songs for the soundtrack of 'The Devil Wears Prada 2,' a sequel to the"}
