[2026-04-29 17:52:58,922][INFO][social_topic_miner.pipeline]: For Sampled Topic id 5: keyword is ['conversion', 'openai', 'certainly', 'advise', 'instagram', 'claim', 'james', 'reject'] and posts are [{'text': "'SNL' writer Jimmy Fowlie announces his missing sister is dead, LAPD investigating as a homicide", 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 0, 'engagement_norm': 0.9101123595505618, 'post_id': '1szagdi', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 20:21:40+00:00'}, {'text': "West Wilson's cousin has been arrested and charged with allegedly murdering their grandmother.", 'platform': 'twitter', 'sub_perspective': 0, 'engagement_norm': 0.7960526315789473, 'post_id': '2049557536312111483', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 18:32:50+00:00'}, {'text': 'Former FBI Director James Comey surrendered to federal authorities today following his indictment over an Instagram photo of seashells spelling out “86 47.” Prosecutors say the post was a threat against President Trump. Comey has denied any violent intent.', 'platform': 'twitter', 'sub_perspective': 1, 'engagement_norm': 0.7236842105263158, 'post_id': '2049552335399960582', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 18:12:10+00:00'}, {'text': 'Former FBI director James Comey has been charged over an Instagram post prosecutors allege threatened Donald Trump’s life. The case centers on a photo of seashells arranged as “8647,” which some interpret as slang for “get rid of 47.” Comey surrendered to law enforcement this', 'platform': 'twitter', 'sub_perspective': 1, 'engagement_norm': 0.9868421052631579, 'post_id': '2049547888750150036', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 17:54:30+00:00'}, {'text': 'Andrew Tate Loses His Lawsuit Over Instagram Banning His Accounts', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 2, 'engagement_norm': 0.8061797752808989, 'post_id': '1sz79gc', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 18:28:08+00:00'}, {'text': 'Streamer Braden “Clavicular” Peters accused of rape and battery in a lawsuit from teen influencer. This article by TMZ summarizes a lawsuit against looksmaxxing influencer Braden Peters accusing him of promising career boosts to a then 16 year old influencer. While she was still underage, Braden transported her to his house where he sexually assaulted her after getting her intoxicated. Braden was a legal adult at the time in 2025. She also accuses him of convincing her he was a doctor and injecting drugs into her face to ‘melt the fat’ against her will.', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 2, 'engagement_norm': 0.9606741573033708, 'post_id': '1sz7vav', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 18:49:00+00:00'}, {'text': 'Musk v. Altman: A Charm Offensive Gone Astray "OpenAI’s lead attorney, William Savitt, used his opening statements to keep the attention on Musk. This is “a tale of two Elons,” Savitt said. According to the defense, Musk originally pledged far more than the tens of millions that he ultimately gave to OpenAI. He reneged on the pledge, and then in 2018, left in a huff because he wasn’t given the keys to the company, Savitt alleged. It was only after OpenAI became a household name, and Musk’s xAI entered the market, that he became “furious” and decided to sue, Savitt claimed."', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 3, 'engagement_norm': 0.398876404494382, 'post_id': '1sz7o8a', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 18:42:14+00:00'}, {'text': 'The Musk v. OpenAI et al. Trial, Day 3 (Part 2): The Judge Can Legally Overturn the Jury\'s Verdict &x200B; What most people don\'t yet realize about this trial is that the jury is there only in an advisory role. While the judge has said that she will probably sustain the jury\'s decision, if they stray from the law or from reason, she can reject their advice and reverse their verdict. This is important because Altman is claiming that Musk is nothing more than a disgruntled donor who is now OpenAI\'s major competitor in the AI race. While the jury might find this ad hominem accusation compelling, the judge knows full well that it is legally inconsequential. The judge will advise the jury about what evidence is applicable, and almost certainly advise them to disregard the disgruntled donor claim. Another claim that Altman is making that the jury might find compelling but that the judge will almost certainly reject is his "yeah, but he did it too" defense. This relates to Musk at one point agreeing with Altman that converting OpenAI to a for-profit made sense. The judge will advise the jury that it was nonetheless Altman, and not Musk, who performed the illegal conversion, and that because Musk wasn\'t involved in the actual conversion process, his prior views on the matter are inconsequential. Another Altman claim that the jury might find compelling, but that the judge will almost certainly find weak and inconsequential, is that at one point Musk wanted total control of the converted for-profit. Again, this doesn\'t absolve Altman of having made the illegal conversion, and perhaps even of having deceived the California Attorney General in order to gain his approval for the conversion. Altman is trying to make this trial about Musk, and while this tactic might sway the jury, it most certainly will not sway the judge.', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 3, 'engagement_norm': 0.28651685393258425, 'post_id': '1sz6eog', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 17:58:50+00:00'}, {'text': 'Erika Kirk calls out Druski and other impersonators: “Every morning I wake up to a new headline lying about me... I have comedians dressing up in whiteface”', 'platform': 'twitter', 'sub_perspective': 4, 'engagement_norm': 0.9342105263157895, 'post_id': '2049588599797031403', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 20:36:16+00:00'}, {'text': 'Erika Kirk says Candace is directly accusing her of being involved in her husband’s assassination. She’s fed up with the comedy skits mocking her: “I have comedians dressing up in whiteface, I have people saying I’m not fit to be CEO, and I have Candace Owens claiming I murdered my husband.”', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 4, 'engagement_norm': 0.9943820224719101, 'post_id': '1sza82d', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 20:13:18+00:00'}] 
