er Apple account could resolve this, but is that the only solution?', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 3, 'engagement_norm': 0.033707865168539325, 'post_id': '1szdkt4', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 22:19:54+00:00'}, {'text': "GPT-5.5 is going to have a party for itself. it chose 5/5 at 5:55 pm for the date and time. if you'd like to come, let us know here: codex will help the team pick people from the replies. 5.5 had some good ideas/requests for the party, which we'll do.", 'platform': 'twitter', 'sub_perspective': 4, 'engagement_norm': 0.2692307692307692, 'post_id': '2049653810558353746', 'created_at': '2026-04-30 00:55:23+00:00'}, {'text': 'Is gemini right about originality? This is what gemini said after talking about creativity and originality: If humans are built of experiences and AI is built of data about those experiences, and both of us "create" by recombining those things (sometimes through mistakes), then the gap between us isn\'t a wall—it\'s just a different shade of the same process.', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 5, 'engagement_norm': 0.38202247191011235, 'post_id': '1sz7kkj', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 18:38:55+00:00'}] 
