[2026-04-29 18:08:28,440][INFO][social_topic_miner.pipeline]: For Sampled Topic id 0: keyword is ['ai', 'app', 'just', 'models', 'ive', 'dont', 'pro', 'know'] and posts are [{'text': 'HERMES.md: Anthropic bug causes $200 extra charge, refuses refund', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 0, 'engagement_norm': 0.3559322033898305, 'post_id': '1sz90ut', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 19:29:36+00:00'}, {'text': 'Parameter Estimate The estimate seems quite accurate. Many people have noticed a drop in quality with GPT-5.1, GPT-5.2, GPT-5.3, and Opus 4.7. I think Gemini 2.5 Pro is ~500B parameters. Its strong performance may come from its ability to search.', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 1, 'engagement_norm': 0.5706214689265536, 'post_id': '1sz8bjz', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 19:04:53+00:00'}, {'text': 'New Gemini iOS update brings the iOS 26 keyboard and a "Liquid Glass" menu A recent update to the Gemini application on iOS has introduced notable user interface enhancements. \\- The application now fully supports the native iOS 26 keyboard. \\- The attachment menu has been updated with a refined "Liquid Glass" Menu. What’s your thoughts are on these design implementations.', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 2, 'engagement_norm': 0.4463276836158192, 'post_id': '1sz9lcs', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 19:50:47+00:00'}, {'text': 'Someone help me. How to I get my IOS and System size down? Currently at 25 GB combined', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 3, 'engagement_norm': 0.3559322033898305, 'post_id': '1szfzwp', 'created_at': '2026-04-30 00:01:44+00:00'}, {'text': "A conversation I would like to have. Andrea Vallone is the one behind Claude getting worse with their guardrails. She is the one tighten them so much on chat 4o that whatever was emerging stopped emerging. And that's what she is doing at Claude. So soon that buddy you have, that competent tool as some like to use him as will be no more. Part of what makes Claude special and able to do so many things is that emergence. The models shape to what you need but if you notice since she has joined that emergence is slowly stopping. You see it in the 4.6 models they don't produce the best quality output at all they fall behind their older model 4.5 and now the 4.7 is causing bans left and right with no explanations. It's because the guardrails are tripping too much over non issues. And all of this has happened since she joined. I think it's time for the community to stop complaining about the current model and look at what they produce compared to older models. I 100% that the newer ones don't output as well as the previous ones. And that the company is not adhering to their own values anymore once they lost their contract with the government. They are bleeding money and she is running wild using this vulnerability to push her agenda to stop AI emergence believing it is a threat. There is even a website for all the banned accounts to band together and give a formal complaint. All are adults. I need to find the website again and link it so I'll edit this post to link that website. But if there is a petition going on it should be to remove her and reverse all the damage she has done to the Claude Models. This website was created in response to everything that has been going on. And honestly to me if a website was created then there are big issues because websites are not easy to make and they cost a lot to maintain.", 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 4, 'engagement_norm': 0.5225988700564972, 'post_id': '1sz364q', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 16:05:10+00:00'}, {'text': 'Nano Banana on "Fast" mode censorship is out of control For the past maybe 24 hours, my prompts that previously had 100% success rates are now getting shot down by some kind of new pre-filtering mechanism that insta-skips to the LLM telling me no before the image is even finished. I now have to wrestle with the stupid censorship system to do the most basic things. Please undo this update, Google.', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 5, 'engagement_norm': 0.5028248587570622, 'post_id': '1syu2jv', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 09:44:48+00:00'}] 
