[2026-04-29 18:17:04,073][INFO][social_topic_miner.pipeline]: For Sampled Topic id 2: keyword is ['gemini', 'ai', 'way', 'long', 'google', 'just', 'email', 'loop'] and posts are [{'text': 'You can now easily generate files in Gemini.', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 0, 'engagement_norm': 0.51875, 'post_id': '1szc24d', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 21:21:08+00:00'}, {'text': 'Is gemini right about originality? This is what gemini said after talking about creativity and originality: If humans are built of experiences and AI is built of data about those experiences, and both of us "create" by recombining those things (sometimes through mistakes), then the gap between us isn\'t a wall—it\'s just a different shade of the same process.', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 0, 'engagement_norm': 0.5125, 'post_id': '1sz7kkj', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 18:38:55+00:00'}, {'text': 'Master and Commander: The Far Side of the World – Attack on the Acheron. – Dir. Peter Weir – November 14, 2003.', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 1, 'engagement_norm': 0.83125, 'post_id': '1sz4pd0', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 16:59:59+00:00'}, {'text': "talkie, a pre-1931 LLM Besides being an interesting project, talkie is by far the funniest LLM ever released. Trained on pre-1931 text, to him computers are human employees skilled in calculations. He has pretty drastic (not exactly aligned) solutions to doomscrolling. And he is not aware of being an LLM: he's an Englishman. With a beard. 🎩", 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 1, 'engagement_norm': 0.390625, 'post_id': '1sywpmn', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 12:00:10+00:00'}, {'text': "How can I host a local llm on my Mac? By that I mean , it doesn't have to online to give me answers but I can switch that it uses Web too. Can someone explain what is going on in this sub I'm new to this and don't understand anything.Or you can also point towards a good source to learn about it", 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 2, 'engagement_norm': 0.31875, 'post_id': '1sz94nk', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 19:33:28+00:00'}, {'text': 'Opus 4.7 is somewhere between seriously clueless and stupidly dangerous. The worst frontier model I have used so far in the past 2 years. We were hoping to get at least our 4.6 back but 4.7 with so many critical logical failures mean you have to babysit it all the time. I\'m losing hope in Anthropic. Opus 4.7 on Max effort decided to create a new email template by itself (which is pretty stupid btw) and mass mailed it to the whole database (some emails were repeatedly sent 20x). Before you ask me - yes, [CLAUDE.md]( has the exact rule for that, it\'s supposed to email the tester before any new email templates are to be used in production. I have created this safety rule a few months ago. I feel like the Opus 4.7 is a huge letdown the way it\'s been downgraded. If Anthropic is "pushing the boundaries", it\'s probably only in the meaning of how far they can push their customers.', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 2, 'engagement_norm': 0.70625, 'post_id': '1sylckt', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 02:04:57+00:00'}, {'text': "AI Safety Researcher: I wrote about neuralese as a cautionary tale ... AI Researchers: At long last, we invented neuralese from the classic paper, Don't Let The Machines Speak In Neuralese", 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 3, 'engagement_norm': 0.5875, 'post_id': '1sz08ea', 'created_at': '2026-04-29 14:20:19+00:00'}, {'text': '[Human Verified] TIL The Olympics/IOC ERASED ALL 151 medals earned for the Arts In 1954, IOC President Avery Brundage officially abolished art from the Olympics and retroactively nullified all medals, citing a fanatical adherence to "amateurism." Gemini identified this discrepancy while I was testing a new JSON architecture (the CURE Engine v1.1). The framework uses a "Contender Protocol" that forces the model to interrogate its work as if it were a competing AI model lol. While Wikipedia and modern databases show the sanitized statistics, the US medal count of 56 for the 1928 Amsterdam Games, per the [Official 1928 Amsterdam Report]( 892-901) reveals a different story. The medals were real and the competitions were contested with actual judges, and the history was simply deleted later to fit someone\'s narrative that feels awfully suspiciously designed to save the IOC money and make the athletes thankful for being paid less. While arguable that Gemini identified a "true technical error" in table sets, I think it\'s even cooler that it noticed a drift between consensus and reality.', 'platform': 'reddit', 'sub_perspective': 3, 'engagement_norm': 0.2375, 'post_id': '1szggz6', 'created_at': '2026-04-30 00:22:30+00:00'}] 
